Hello! My name is Rhylie Ladoucer and I am an undergrad at Clemson University
studying genetics and biochemistry. I am currently in the process of
developing a custom social media scraper for Dr. Ennis's Creative Inquiry
involved in debunking pseudoscience and exposing the predatory 
tactics of the wellness industry. Thank you for taking the time to
look through my code! 

___________

### The Spiel:
Many people have fallen prey to the charlatans of the wellness industry,
who are often parading around on social media, and have suffered as a 
consequence of placing their trust in these demagogues. Many of whom 
were already suffering from pre-existing conditions, and are now being 
"prescribed" bogus treatments that either provide nothing of aid, or 
backfire and cause even more harm. 

It's absolutely no secret that the wellness industry has a knack for targeting the vulnerable; desperation is one hell of a drug. 

Someone clawing for just an ounce of hope in their distress is precisely the type of victim the wellness industry seeks. Sugar-coated language, cutesy designs, and a carefully cultivated sense of safety are some of the many tactics employed by benefactors of the wellness industry, but perhaps the worst of them all, using empathy as a sales tactic. 

It's one thing to perform these treatments on yourself, but a whole 
different line is crossed when it's your own child, or even your most 
vulnerable loved one.

More and more cases of fad treatments gone wrong are popping up in ERs 
nation and worldwide, some cases where the consequences are irreversible, or fatal.
___________

This is a work in progress, so you may see some unfinished or nonfunctional
code. I'm mainly using this repo as a means of tracking my progress. 